As you will see here I 100% disagree with him on this and as I said in the interview my reason is because what he believes on this topic is unbiblical. If I can’t support what you say with the Bible than I have to strongly disagree with your theology on it. So let’s go to the Bible 📖.. Jessie point was … why would God have to speak to someone else to interpret the words he was speaking through you? Which doesn’t make sense if you are leaning on your own understanding (which the Bible tells us NOT to do in Proverbs 3 verse 5.) 
—
But specifically on the interpretation of tongues, that is actually talked about in 1 Corinthians chapter 14 verses 27-29: If anyone speaks in a tongue, two—or at the most three should speak, one at a time, and someone must interpret.
-
If there is no interpreter, the speaker should keep quiet in the church and speak to himself and God.
-
Two or three prophets should speak, and the others should weigh carefully what is said.
-
If you continue down to verse 30: Therefore, my brothers, be eager to prophesy, and do not forbid speaking in tongues.
-
Also if you go over to Acts chapter 1 verse 5: Jesus says to his disciples, “John baptized with water, but before many days you shall be baptized with the Holy Spirit.” Then in verse 8, he says, “You shall receive power when the Holy Spirit has come upon you; and you shall be my witnesses.”
-
Which brings us to Acts 2 verse 4 - All of them were filled with the Holy Spirit and began to speak in other tongues as the Spirit enabled them.
-
So the gift of tongues also came with the receiving of the Holy Spirit on the day of Pentecost.. 
-
So for your theology to be right you also would have to deny what the Bible said came from the Holy Spirit. 
-
So the Bible says it’s from “God”…. Jesse believes it’s from the “Devil”
